## Architecture Overview

| Layer | Stack | Free Tier |
|---|---|---|
| **Frontend** | React 18 + Tailwind CSS + Framer Motion + Three.js | — |
| **Backend** | Node.js / Express (or Next.js API Routes) | — |
| **Database** | Neon PostgreSQL + Prisma ORM | 0.5 GB storage, 190 compute hours/mo |
| **Auth** | JWT + bcrypt (admin-created credentials) | — |
| **Storage** | Uploadthing (scanned documents & files) | 2 GB storage, 2 GB bandwidth free |
| **Calendar** | Google Calendar API (OAuth 2.0) | Free |
| **Realtime** | Socket.io (comments, notifications) | — |
| **Cache/Queue** | Upstash Redis | 10K commands/day free |
| **Email** | Resend | 3,000 emails/mo free |
| **Hosting** | Vercel (frontend) + Render (backend) | Both have generous free tiers |

### 💡 Why These Free Platforms?

| Service | Why | Free Limit |
|---|---|---|
| **Neon** | Serverless Postgres, auto-suspend on idle, branching for dev/staging | 0.5 GB storage, 190 compute hrs |
| **Uploadthing** | Dead-simple file uploads for Next.js/React, built-in CDN, signed URLs | 2 GB storage, 2 GB bandwidth |
| **Upstash Redis** | Serverless Redis for rate limiting, caching, sessions | 10K commands/day |
| **Resend** | Modern email API, great DX, React Email support | 3,000 emails/mo |
| **Render** | Free web services with auto-deploy from GitHub | 750 hrs/mo |
| **Vercel** | Best-in-class frontend hosting, edge network, preview deploys | 100 GB bandwidth |

