## PHASE 2 — Database Schema & API Foundation

**Duration:** 4–5 days

- Design and migrate Neon PostgreSQL schema via Prisma:
  - Configure Neon project with `main` branch (production) + `dev` branch (development)
  - Use Neon's serverless driver (`@neondatabase/serverless`) for edge-compatible connections
  - Enable connection pooling via Neon's built-in PgBouncer
  ```
  User (id, email, password_hash, role, client_id, avatar, created_at)
  Client (id, company_name, logo, industry, onboarded_at)
  Project (id, client_id, name, description, status, start_date, end_date)
  Document (id, project_id, category, label, file_url, uploaded_by, uploaded_at)
  Milestone (id, project_id, title, description, status, target_date, order)
  MilestoneComment (id, milestone_id, user_id, body, created_at)
  Meeting (id, project_id, title, gcal_event_id, start_time, end_time, link)
  Task (id, project_id, milestone_id, title, start_date, end_date, progress, assignee)
  Invoice (id, client_id, amount, status, due_date, pdf_url, uploaded_by, notes)
  PaymentReminder (id, invoice_id, sent_at, channel)
  ProgressUpdate (id, project_id, user_id, body, percentage, attachments, created_at)
  AdminLog (id, user_id, action, entity_type, entity_id, metadata, created_at)
  ```
- Build Express/Next.js API with versioned routes (`/api/v1/...`)
- Implement middleware: auth guard, rate limiter, error handler, request logger
- Seed database with demo data for development
- Write Postman/Bruno collection for all endpoints

**Deliverable:** Fully documented REST API with seed data and test suite.

