## PHASE 15 — Security Hardening & Audit

**Duration:** 3–4 days

- **Authentication Security:**
  - Implement 2FA (TOTP via authenticator app)
  - Session timeout with configurable idle duration
  - IP allowlisting option for enterprise clients
  - Audit log: every login, failed attempt, password change
- **API Security:**
  - Input sanitization on all endpoints (express-validator / zod)
  - SQL injection prevention (Prisma parameterized queries)
  - XSS prevention (CSP headers, output encoding)
  - CSRF protection for cookie-based auth
  - Rate limiting per endpoint with Upstash Redis (free tier)
- **Data Security:**
  - Encrypt sensitive fields at rest (AES-256)
  - TLS 1.3 enforced for all connections (Neon enforces SSL by default)
  - Database backups: Neon built-in point-in-time recovery (7-day history on free)
  - GDPR-ready: data export and deletion endpoints
- **Penetration Testing:**
  - Run OWASP ZAP automated scan
  - Manual testing of auth flows, file uploads, API boundaries
  - Fix all critical and high-severity findings

**Deliverable:** Hardened, audited portal ready for production with enterprise-grade security.

